last_episode_to_air.name: Johnny's Last Chapter
last_episode_to_air.overview: Johnny and Dukey are sucked into a history book.

name: Johnny Test
overview: Young Johnny is gung-ho and full of courage. Johnny's brainiac twin sisters, Susan and Mary, use Johnny as their guinea pig for their outrageous scientific experiments. If they can dream it up, Johnny will do it; as long as his genetically engineered super dog, Dukey, can come along.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

Johnny Test started its first season on Kids' WB on September 17, 2005 with the first episodes "Johnny to the Center of the Earth" and "Johnny X" and ended on July 29, 2006 with episodes "Johnny Dodgeball" and "Johnny and the Attack of the Monster Truck". This was the only season to be traditionally animated, as the next seasons are animated in Flash, in order to save the show's budget money.

This season, along with season 2, was released on DVD in a bundle on February 15, 2011 in Region 1. It was also released on DVD on February 21, 2008 in Region 2.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. Johnny Test started its second season on October 28, 2006 with "Hoist the Johnny Roger" and "Johnny's Turbo Toy Force" and ended on May 12, 2007 with episodes "The Good, the Bad, and the Johnny" and "Rock-a-Bye Johnny".

This season, along with its first season, was released on DVD in a bundle on February 15, 2011 in Region 1.

This season marks the first appearance for Ashleigh Ball as the new voice of Mary Test, Sissy Blakely, and Missy.

This season, along with the fourth season, was released on DVD in a bundle on September 13, 2011 in Region 1.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

Johnny Test started its fourth season on September 10, 2009, containing 26 full episodes. It was the first season to premiere on Teletoon first. This is the first season to be produced in high definition. This season began airing on Cartoon Network on November 9, 2009. This would be the final season for Louis Chirillo and Ashleigh Ball as the voices of Dukey, Mary Test, and Sissy Blakely, although Ball returns later to resume her roles in Season 6.

This season, along with the third season, was released on DVD in a bundle on September 13, 2011 in Region 1.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

On August 24, 2010, it was announced that Johnny Test was renewed for a fifth season. The renewal brought up the series total to 91 episodes.

Johnny Test started its fifth season on June 13, 2011, in the US. This was the first season to premiere on Cartoon Network first. This is also the first season for Trevor Devall as the new voice of Dukey, and Brittney Wilson, who departed from the show after season 1, to return to play Mary Test, Sissy Blakely, and Missy. In August 2012, Netflix released the fifth season of Johnny Test as part of its Cartoon Network series releases.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

The sixth season of Johnny Test was ordered in the early March season. It began airing on April 3, 2013, starting with the episode "Johnny on the Clock" on Cartoon Network in the United States.

This season will feature its 100th episode, making it the first Teletoon series and the fourth Cartoon Network to pass the 100-episode milestone. According to creator Scott Fellows, the 100th episode will be a half-hour special.

This season is the first to broadcast in high-definition on Cartoon Network in the United States.

This season also features the re-appearance of Ashleigh Ball, who departed from the show after the fourth season, due to working on other projects.

episodes.name: Johnny to the Center of the Earth
episodes.overview: Things have been mysteriously disappearing underground, making Johnny and Dukey believe that the people behind this are "mole people". When Johnny accidentally loses his dad's new camera, he must journey to the center of the earth to retrieve it before dinnertime, or he will be grounded.

episodes.name: Johnny X
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary give Gil a piece of their special love "bubble gum", but by accident, it makes him transform. In order to save Gil and the others in pork belly, they have to give Johnny and Dukey some cool super powers.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Bling-Bling Boy
episodes.overview: Bling-Bling Boy has stolen a device that turns things into gold and Johnny must get it back before dinnertime.

episodes.name: Johnny Impossible
episodes.overview: Johnny tries to get his baseball back from an old man before the baseball game starts.

episodes.name: Johnny Test: Party Monster
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary are having a party and use a device on Johnny in order to make him look good so all the girls at the party will love him, but Johnny turns into a monster.

episodes.name: Johnny Test: Extreme Crime Stopper
episodes.overview: The Extreme Teen Team are on the loose and it's up to Johnny to bring them down.

episodes.name: Deep Sea Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny uses an invention to breathe underwater, yet sharks and electric eels begin to walk on land and wreak havoc to the beach.

episodes.name: Johnny and the Amazing Turbo Action Backpack
episodes.overview: Bling-Bling Boy steals a backpack and Johnny must retrieve it so Susan and Mary can show it off at the school science fair.

episodes.name: Johnny and the Ice Pigs
episodes.overview: Johnny goes back in time to ask Thomas Edison for a hockey invention and then to gather all of the vicious and ruthless "legends" he could find, in order to form a hockey team which will help the Ice Pigs win a game.

episodes.name: Johnny’s House of Horrors
episodes.overview: Johnny fills the house with some of Hugh's favorite things listed in his notebook. However, Johnny learns that the book was also full of Hugh's least favorite things (most of them scary.) To make matters worse, Lila's boss is coming over for dinner that night.

episodes.name: Johnny’s Super Smartypants
episodes.overview: Johnny wears super smarty pants in order to win the love of a genius girl, Janet Nelson Jr. But later, the pants get a mind of their own.

episodes.name: Take Your Johnny to Work Day
episodes.overview: Johnny sneaks into Lila's car along with Susan and Mary on Take Your Daughter to Work Day, thinking that it's unfair that girls don't have to go to school on this day, but boys do. When the kids get to Lila's workplace, they sneak into a lab and accidentally release a missile.

episodes.name: Johnny and the Mega Roboticles
episodes.overview: Johnny brings a toy, Nasteria, to life. But the toy decides to destroy Porkbelly. Now Johnny needs to stop the evil action figure with a toy force, led by Nasteria's arch enemy, Mega Roboticle.

episodes.name: Johnny Gets Mooned
episodes.overview: Johnny steals a rocket his sisters made to travel to the moon so he can write his report. Unexpectedly, he battles some moon monsters and rescues Canadian astronauts.

episodes.name: Johnny Hollywood
episodes.overview: Johnny uses a gadget to travel into a movie, The Quickest and the Monkiest. But what happens when the gadget gets stuck and the movie has a bad ending?

episodes.name: Johnny's Turbo Time Rewinder
episodes.overview: Johnny's sisters invent a time rewinder that can go back up to 5 minutes and they use it to get Johnny in trouble. Infuriated, he tries multiple times to steal this, but he fails; eventually, he gets a similar one from Bling-Bling Boy.

episodes.name: Return of Johnny X
episodes.overview: Johnny becomes Johnny X again in order to take down Bling-Bling's latest evil invention, Repto-Slicer.

episodes.name: Sonic Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey try Susan and Mary's ultimate scooter and are wanted in the future.

episodes.name: Dog Days of Johnny
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary put a device on Dukey, making him respond to their every command. Now Johnny must stop Susan and Mary, and get his best friend back.

episodes.name: Johnny's Pink Plague
episodes.overview: Johnny uses a device to free everyone of zits.

episodes.name: Johnny's Extreme Game Controller
episodes.overview: Johnny uses his game controller to control people, but Hugh gets his hands on it and begins affecting Johnny in the process.

episodes.name: Li'l Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny accidentally shrinks himself and Dukey into a sub-atomic universe while shrinking his toys. Unexpectedly, its nature turns against him.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Brain Freezer
episodes.overview: A kid at Susan and Mary's school becomes a villain named Brain Freezer. Now Johnny must stop this villain and unfreeze everyone he froze.

episodes.name: Johnny's Big Snow Job
episodes.overview: Johnny uses a device in Susan and Mary's lab to make it snow outside.

episodes.name: Johnny Dodgeball
episodes.overview: Johnny uses a bionic arm to magnify his arm strength to beat Sissy at dodge ball. However, it breaks after being exposed to cereal.

episodes.name: Johnny and the Attack of the Monster Truck
episodes.overview: Eugene brings a living monster truck to the Test house, and it began to be enraged after Eugene kicked it because it didn't win Susan's heart. Now the truck wants to destroy the entire monster truck species. It's up to Johnny to figure out how to stop it.

episodes.name: Hoist the Johnny Roger
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey must help a pathetic pirate, Nobeard, take down his powerful brother pirate, Blackbeard, and impress his father, Greybeard. Johnny goes back to the future to get his sisters' help.

episodes.name: Johnny's Turbo Toy Force
episodes.overview: An evil toymaker named Wacko gives out robots to all the children of Porkbelly, which imprison them. The gang seeks assistance from the Turbo Toy Force.

episodes.name: JTV
episodes.overview: Johnny starts his own channel over a channel which only broadcast emergencies and tests. Later, the army needs the channel for a runaway plane.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Bling-Bling Boy 2
episodes.overview: Eugene creates a device that turns himself, Johnny, and Dukey into young children, interfering with Johnny's video game showdown with Sissy.

episodes.name: Johnnyland
episodes.overview: Johnny makes a theme park called Johnnyland in the backyard. However, Hugh demands the park be torn down, later stumbling into an unstable ride with Lila.

episodes.name: Johnny's Got a Brand New Dad
episodes.overview: Hugh's constant sayings of "no" begin to infuriate Johnny, so, with Susan and Mary's help, they make a new one. However, when the new dad gets exposed to the plutonium he got for Susan and Mary, things start to turn out ugly.

episodes.name: Saturday's Alright for Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny is trying to have the perfect Saturday, but Sissy ruins it by trying to practice William Tell archery on Johnny. Johnny then uses Susan and Mary's Saturday Repeater machine to try again.

episodes.name: Johnny Mint Chip
episodes.overview: Johnny, Dukey, and the sisters go to an ice cream factory, in order to get the recipe for mint chip ice cream which Johnny and Dukey can't stop eating.

episodes.name: Johnny's Pet Day
episodes.overview: Dukey gets jealous when Johnny takes Repto-Slicer to school for pet day and not him. However, this lands him into danger of becoming a TV star.

episodes.name: Phat Johnny
episodes.overview: An accident in Eugene's lab leaves Johnny overweight like him. Johnny uses his weight to become a rapper and to get a video game that he wanted. However, karma is after him and ruins his experience.

episodes.name: The Revenge of Johnny X
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey must rescue Susan from Bling-Bling Boy in the forms of Johnny X and Super Pooch. Little do they know she doesn't want to be rescued, as Bling-Bling Boy has taken her on a cruise bot with a swimming pool, movie theater, anti-gravity chamber, video arcade, and her favorite restaurants among other luxuries.

episodes.name: The Enchanted Land of Johnnia
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey catch rainy day boredom, and use one of the sisters' devices, thinking that it is an inter-dimensional travel machine, and go into a land known as Johnnia.

episodes.name: 101 Johnnies
episodes.overview: Johnny makes 100 robot clones in order to do his chores for him, but the clones become defective soon after.

episodes.name: Johnny Zombie Tea Party
episodes.overview: Johnny brings Porkbelly's founders back to life in order to help with his report.

episodes.name: Johnny Test in Black & White
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey shrink themselves, and end up in Mr. Black's stomach and brain to make him forget that the General told Mr. Black and Mr. White to spy on Susan and Mary to stop them from doing dangerous experiments.

episodes.name: Johnny the Kid
episodes.overview: Johnny and his family go on vacation to a dude ranch on Susan and Mary's choice, but it is invaded by an outlaw motorcycle club shortly after they arrive. With the help from Bling-Bling Boy and Gil, both whom have also been taken a trip to the ranch, the Tests resolve to stop the bikers from ruining their fun and take back their holiday.

episodes.name: Downhill Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny goes to the Behemoth, the ultimate downhill ski resort. However, he has to find ways to go downhill since the ski captain doesn't let kids go.

episodes.name: Johnny Meets the Pork-Ness Monsters
episodes.overview: It is a hot day and Johnny's family cannot seem to find a place where they can cool off and get wet. They go to Lake Pork-Ness, which is rumored to have a monster inhabitant. Susan and Mary believe that the idea is a total myth and try to prove there are no monsters in the lake.

episodes.name: Johnny X Strikes Back
episodes.overview: Five evil villains who have been defeated previously by Johnny (Wacko, the Bee Keeper, Brain Freezer, Mr. Mittens and Albert the butler) team up and kidnap him. Now it's up to Susan, Mary, Dukey, Bling-Bling, Gil, and Bumper to save him.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Super Soaking Cyborgs
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary create Gil cyborgs to make Gil jealous but they try to eliminate Gil and anyone in their path. It's up to Johnny to stop them. Meanwhile, the girls keep Gil "safe" in a box in their lab.

episodes.name: 00-Johnny
episodes.overview: Tim Burnout steals blueprints of the girls' original plan to alternate Dukey and uses it on his cat, Mr. Mittens. But he becomes evil and now it's up to Johnny and Dukey to stop him.

episodes.name: Johnny of the Jungle
episodes.overview: While on a class trip to the safari park with Dukey disguised as Johnny's dad, Johnny and Dukey decide to help animals get to their homeland in Africa.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Smash Badger 3
episodes.overview: While trying to figure out some cheat codes from his video game, Johnny accidentally brings Smash Badger to life.

episodes.name: Johnny Bee Good
episodes.overview: The Bee Keeper steals all the candy in Porkbelly and it's up to Johnny, Dukey, and the girls to stop him.

episodes.name: The Good, the Bad & the Johnny
episodes.overview: To control Johnny's frequent bad behavior, the girls split his bad genes to make his genes 100% good. The bad gene later gets a life of its own, making two Johnnys, one nice and one evil.

episodes.name: Rock-a-Bye Johnny
episodes.overview: Dukey keeps Johnny up all night with his pillow fights and Johnny goes to the sisters to get some sleep. But Johnny misfires and causes his parents to go sleepwalking.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

Johnny Test started its second season on October 28, 2006 with "Hoist the Johnny Roger" and "Johnny's Turbo Toy Force" and ended on May 12, 2007 with episodes "The Good, the Bad, and the Johnny" and "Rock-a-Bye Johnny".

This season, along with its first season, was released on DVD in a bundle on February 15, 2011 in Region 1.

This season marks the first appearance for Ashleigh Ball as the new voice of Mary Test, Sissy Blakely, and Missy.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Bling-Bling Boy 3
episodes.overview: When Eugene finds out that Johnny is what stands in the way of him and Susan, he sets out to lock Johnny up forever as he tries to get the last ingredient for his sister's "Susan-hating lozenge".

episodes.name: Stinkin' Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny wants to buy an HDTV and the twins need an important ingredient for their experiment. The only solution: Enter Johnny in a professional wrestling competition so they can win $10,000, so they make Johnny a wrestling suit which allows him to spray stink gas from his suit.

episodes.name: Johnny X and the Attack of the Snowmen
episodes.overview: Brain Freezer creates an army of snowmen, and only Johnny X can stop him.

episodes.name: Johnny vs. Dukey
episodes.overview: After Johnny and Dukey send Bumper packing, they start to come against each other in a game of "Say Uncle".

episodes.name: Here Johnny, Here Boy
episodes.overview: Fed up with the lack of respect, Dukey has convinced Mary and Susan to turn Johnny into a dog. In the meantime Mary and Susan turn themselves into animals so they can get loved by Gil. It all goes wrong when Animal Control arrives and snatches them.

episodes.name: Johnny Applesauce
episodes.overview: After hearing about American heroes in Social Studies class, Johnny decides to help his classmates by bringing back applesauce as a vigilante after the Lunch Lady outlaws it. However, this lands him into trouble.

episodes.name: Johnny'mon
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey are transported into their favorite video game, Tiny'Mon, but they end up trapped and must defeat Blast Ketchup, and his Tiny'Mon Kadoomerang, to get back home, with only the seemingly useless Cuddlebuns for protection.

episodes.name: Bath Time for Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny refuses to bathe, and his family forcibly attempts to wash him. Meanwhile, Dukey is mad because he thinks Johnny forgot his birthday.

episodes.name: Johnny Test: Monster Starter
episodes.overview: Mr. Black and Mr. White ask Susan and Mary to design a new weapon, so they make a helmet that allows the user to control things with their mind. But it becomes a huge mistake when it's stuck on Johnny's head, and his obsession with a new video game now makes any inanimate object he sees turn into a monster.

episodes.name: Johnny Holiday
episodes.overview: Johnny is upset because the holidays that give free candy to the world are spread too far apart, so Johnny decides to start his own holiday, known as Kids Get Free Candy Day, and try to spread free candy. When there are some adult protests against this holiday, Johnny, Dukey, Susan, and Mary gain an unlikely ally against this – the Beekeeper.

episodes.name: Coming to a Johnny Near You
episodes.overview: When Dukey explains how narration makes everything seem better, Johnny convinces Susan and Mary to make a reality warping megaphone, but it malfunctions.

episodes.name: When Johnny Comes Marching Home
episodes.overview: Johnny buys a video game which turns out to be a military plot to recruit an elite team of super soldiers, and then he must join the fight against a group of renegade penguins who are losing their home to global warming.

episodes.name: Johnnyitis
episodes.overview: Johnny drinks an unstable isotope so he can get sick and not have to study for a test for school. Unfortunately, not only does the isotope give him red spots and a purple tongue, if it's not cured within four hours, it's going to give him immense bloating, cause violent coughing, and eventually make him explode.

episodes.name: Johnny Mustache
episodes.overview: Johnny has his sisters use an invention that will give him a mustache so that Johnny can get into a movie meant for older people. But when Bling Bling Boy pesters Johnny to use the invention on him, Johnny shoots the invention at him too much and now Eugene looks like the monster from a movie.

episodes.name: Johnny Fu
episodes.overview: When Bumper uses kung fu moves to take over the school, Johnny seeks Dukey's kung fu advice, but to no avail.

episodes.name: Johnny Escape From Bling Bling Island
episodes.overview: Bling-Bling Boy steals Susan and Mary's shoes, and it is up to Johnny and a reluctant Dukey to retrieve them before their dinner with Gil.

episodes.name: Johnny's Monkey Business
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary need to get Lolo away from Johnny and Dukey for various tests when they try to make a profit out of her in order to get a video game system.

episodes.name: Johnny Bench
episodes.overview: Johnny must make a bench for woodshop class or he goes to summer school.

episodes.name: Johnny Kart Racing
episodes.overview: All Johnny and Dukey want is a simple bike race between the two of them; but everyone joins the race.

episodes.name: Johnny Smells Good
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey test a perfume experiment and now everyone is attracted to them. They use this to their advantage, but it goes out of control.

episodes.name: Return of Johnny'mon
episodes.overview: Seeking revenge, Blast Ketchup sucks Hugh into the Tiny'Mon world, trying to suck Johnny in. Thinking he is one of Johnny's Tiny'Mon, he captures him. Johnny, Dukey, Susan, and Mary must stop him. To re-exit the game, they must win another battle with Blast.

episodes.name: Johnny Dukey Doo
episodes.overview: When a condemned hotel gets haunted by ghosts Susan and Mary drag Johnny, Dukey and Gil into the house to prove that the ghosts are fake.

episodes.name: Johnny X: A New Beginning
episodes.overview: It's time for the Earth Day Carnival and the Johnny Stopping Evil Force 5 (with Zizrar replacing the Beekeeper) returns and obtains the same mutant powers as Johnny X, and Super Dukey.

episodes.name: Johnny X: The Final Ending
episodes.overview: Following the events right after "JX6-a: A New Beginning" Dark Vegan returns to destroy the Earth with an upgraded armada. Dark Vegan, with his upgrade armada, is cutting up the Earth's trees, taking off the oxygen and sucking up the Earth's water. Johnny, Dukey, and the Johnny Stopping Evil Force 5 team up to stop Dark Vegan and return the Earth's resources.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. This season, along with the fourth season, was released on DVD in a bundle on September 13, 2011 in Region 1.

episodes.name: Johnny's New Baby Sisters
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary purposely turn themselves into babies while the parents are out, and Johnny has to keep them safe from the irresponsible babysitter Gil; this interferes with a party he and Dukey had been planning.

episodes.name: Porta Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny tricks his sisters into letting him have teleporting powers. Susan and Mary mess with the powers to get revenge. Later the twins accidentally get them caught in a middle of an art robbery.

episodes.name: Join the Johnny Scouts
episodes.overview: After Johnny lands his bike into a garbage truck, he becomes a Lady Bird Scout and tries to sell 1,000 boxes of cookies to get a new one. Little does he know, Sissy wants the bike as well, but for a better reason.

episodes.name: Johnny BC
episodes.overview: Johnny goes back in time in order to get a sloth bone for the twins, but when he returns he becomes a caveman, interfering with his grounding from selling Hugh's personal items.

episodes.name: Runaway Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey run away when Johnny's parents say he's old enough to do chores but not old enough to watch PG-13 movies.

episodes.name: Johnny on the Spot
episodes.overview: Johnny steals a portable black hole, which later creates an early apocalypse.

episodes.name: Dark Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny joins forces with Dark Vegan to get him back to his home planet.

episodes.name: No Homework for Johnny
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary build Johnny a robot in order to help him do his homework, but the robot ends up stealing things for Johnny.

episodes.name: Papa Johnny
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary switch Johnny and Hugh's brains after the two make a bet that involves taking on each other's lives.

episodes.name: The Johnnyminster Dog Show
episodes.overview: Johnny and Dukey try to get in a dog show which only allows perfectly groomed and trained dogs.

episodes.name: Dukey Jekyll and Johnny Hyde
episodes.overview: Dukey drinks a liquid which makes him turn into a monster. To make matters worse, a dog catcher (and later Mr. Black and Mr. White) are after him.

episodes.name: Johnny's Trophy Case
episodes.overview: Johnny wants to get a trophy to put in his trophy case. Susan and Mary get obsessed with winning, so the three of them enter The Pork Belly River Jumpoff to win 1 million dollars and a trophy.

episodes.name: Johnny's Amazing Cookie Company
episodes.overview: Susan and Mary make fortune cookies that come true, and Johnny sells them with the typical drastic results.

episodes.name: Johnny's Big Dumb Sisters
episodes.overview: The twins' latest invention accidentally makes them dumb thanks to Johnny right before their scholarship interview.

episodes.name: My Johnny Guard
episodes.overview: - Johnny gets hired to stop Bling-bling from kissing Susan, but Johnny turns on the sisters once Bling-Bling bribes him.

episodes.name: Tom and Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny turns into a mouse for Susan and Mary, but when Mr. Mittens comes, things get chaotic. This episode is a parody of Tom and Jerry.

episodes.name: Quantum of Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny tries to get invited to a party to stop a villain. NOTE: Susan and Mary don't appear in this episode.

episodes.name: Johnny Get Yer Gum
episodes.overview: Mr. Whacko invents a new helium gum that lifts kids into the sky, and Johnny must save them.

episodes.name: Old School Johnny
episodes.overview: Johnny travels to 1845 when school was easier, but he gets stuck there because the power supplier to the Turbo Time Tea house hasn't been invented yet. The sisters and Johnny try to find outdated technology to power the tea house.

episodes.name: Johnny Degrees Below Zero
episodes.overview: Johnny creates a magnetic force field on the Earth which makes Porkbelly the new north pole.

episodes.name: Johnny Johnny

4.name: Season 4
4.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

Johnny Test started its fourth season on September 10, 2009, containing 26 full episodes. It was the first season to premiere on Teletoon first. This is the first season to be produced in high definition. This season began airing on Cartoon Network on November 9, 2009. This would be the final season for Louis Chirillo and Ashleigh Ball as the voices of Dukey, Mary Test, and Sissy Blakely, although Ball returns later to resume her roles in Season 6.

This season, along with the third season, was released on DVD in a bundle on September 13, 2011 in Region 1.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian/American animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

On August 24, 2010, it was announced that Johnny Test was renewed for a fifth season. The renewal brought up the series total to 91 episodes.

Johnny Test started its fifth season on June 13, 2011, in the US. This was the first season to premiere on Cartoon Network first. This is also the first season for Trevor Devall as the new voice of Dukey, and Brittney Wilson, who departed from the show after season 1, to return to play Mary Test, Sissy Blakely, and Missy. In August 2012, Netflix released the fifth season of Johnny Test as part of its Cartoon Network series releases.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview:
Johnny Test is a Canadian animated television series. It premiered on Kids' WB, on The WB Television Network, on September 17, 2005. The series currently airs in the United States on Cartoon Network, as of January 7, 2008, and in Canada on Teletoon, as of October 28, 2006. The show was produced by Cookie Jar Entertainment for its second and later seasons. The series is rated TV-Y7 for the first four seasons, and TV-Y7-FV for the fifth.

The sixth season of Johnny Test was ordered in the early March season. It began airing on April 3, 2013, starting with the episode "Johnny on the Clock" on Cartoon Network in the United States.

This season will feature its 100th episode, making it the first Teletoon series and the fourth Cartoon Network to pass the 100-episode milestone. According to creator Scott Fellows, the 100th episode will be a half-hour special.

This season is the first to broadcast in high-definition on Cartoon Network in the United States.

This season also features the re-appearance of Ashleigh Ball, who departed from the show after the fourth season, due to working on other projects.
